      • getPortlist

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getPortlist()
        Gets the value of the portlist property. This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the portlist property. For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 
         getPortlist().add(newItem);
        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list String
        Returns:
        value of the portList property.
